author: Staff reports
title: Prep rewind: Zeeland West volleyball 1st in OK Green; Zeeland swim tops BC
text: Posted Oct. 13, 2015 at 10:47 PM Updated at 10:47 PM Posted Oct. 13, 2015 at 10:47 PM Holland, Mich. The Zeeland West volleyball team defeated Byron Center in a five-set thriller on Tuesday to take over sole possession of first place in the OK Green. The Dux won 25-14, 18-25, 25-19, 23-25, 15-12 to improve to 7-1 in the OK Green and 25-14 overall. Zeeland West can claim at least a share of a league title with a win Thursday at Holland Christian. The Dux were led by Kinsey Arendsen with 16 kills and Kayla Burrows with 15 kills. Aubrey Wilson had 40 assists to lead a balanced attack that saw five different Dux with five kills or more. The defense was again anchored by Chloe Veldhof who had 28 digs. Girls swimming Zeeland 100, Byron Center 86 The No. 8 Zeeland girls swim team honored its senior class and put itself in position to clinch the regular-season OK Green Conference title. Senior Morgan Bullock won the 200-yard individual medley (2 minutes, 7.49 seconds) and the 100 butterfly (57.21), going 1-2 with fellow senior Janise Everest (1:00.81). Everest won the 100 breaststroke (1:05.82). Senior Paige Hoeve won the 100 freestyle (55.42). Claire Meeuwsen won the 50 freestyle (25.22). Jenna Schrotenboer won the 200 freestyle (1:59.48) and the 500 freestyle (5:30.36). Josie Smith won diving (204.2 points). Holland 99, Hamilton 84 With an a different line-up in place, the girls did well responding to adversity. Great swims out of Anna Giesler (200 free, 100 fly), Clara Steeby (200 IM, 100 Back), Claire Cebelak (50, 100 free) and Emily Nightingale (200 IM, 100 Breast). Holland Christian 110, Unity Christian 74 Valerie Edewaard won the 200 freestyle in a Division 3 state cut of 2:05.44 and the 100 butterfly in 1:04.43, another state cut. Hannah Visser won the 500 freestyle (5:35.51) in a D3 cut. Taylor Moralez won the 200 individual medley (2:29.35). Katherine Heeres won the 50 freestyle (25.8) and qualified for state in the 100 breaststroke. Areal Tolsma won diving (190.6). Volleyball The Saugatuck volleyball team defeated rival Fennville 25-17, 25-21, 25-16 on Tuesday. The Indians improved to 12-14-2. Maggie Shanahan totaled nine kills, 12 digs and 18 assists to lead Saugatuck. Lauren Greene had five blocks, six kills, eight digs and two aces. Madison DeWitt had 14 digs and six kills. Alyssa Alexander had 10 digs. Kiri Tiemeyer had eight kills and four blocks. Tori Kunkel and six digs and four kills. Taylor Kunkel had 10 assists and nine digs. Hamilton 3, Holland 0 The Hawkeyes won 25-17, 25-22, 25-12. Hamilton's Britney VandeWege had 24 assists, Frannie Prins had 17 digs and Nicole Dekker had eight kills. Holland's Juliana Dykstra had 19 assists. Boys soccer GR Union 1, Zeeland East 0 The Chix lost the OK Black match. Kalamazoo Home School 4, Holland Calvary 0 Hunter Baumann made 10 saves in goal for the Crusaders (3-13). By Staff reports
